agna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Felicia de Throckmorton was born in 1145, in Throckmorton, Worcestershire, England as the daughter of Osmond de Throckmorton and Felicia de Warwick. She married Bryan de Derinstone about 1173, in Coughton, Warwickshire, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. She died in 1215, in Coughton, Warwickshire, England, at the age of 70."},"et":{"1145–1215":"1145–1215","1140–1177":"1140–1177","1146–1176":"1146–1176","1145–1202":"1145–1202","1175–1246":"1175–1246","1180–1215":"1180–1215","1110–1154":"1110–1154","–Female":"Surnud","about 1173":"umbes 1173","1154":"1154","1110":"1110","1176":"1176","1175":"1175","1140":"1140","1180":"1180","1215":"1215","1202":"1202","1246":"1246","1146":"1146","1145":"1145","about 1139":"umbes 1139","1177":"1177","about 1154":"umbes 1154","Worcestershire, England":"Worcestershire, England","Throckmorton, Worcestershire, England":"Throckmorton, Worcestershire, England","Worcester, Worcestershire, England":"Worcester, Worcestershire, England","Coughton, Warwickshire, England":"Coughton, Warwickshire, England","England":"England"},"fi":{"1145–1215":"1145–1215","1140–1177":"1140–1177","1146–1176":"1146–1176","1145–1202":"1145–1202","1175–1246":"1175–1246","1180–1215":"1180–1215","1110–1154":"1110–1154","–Female":"Kuollut","about 1173":"noin 1173","1154":"1154","1110":"1110","1176":"1176","1175":"1175","1140":"1140","1180":"1180","1215":"1215","1202":"1202","1246":"1246","1146":"1146","1145":"1145","about 1139":"noin 1139","1177":"1177","about 1154":"noin 1154","Worcestershire, England":"Worcestershire, England","Throckmorton, Worcestershire, England":"Throckmorton, Worcestershire, England","Worcester, Worcestershire, England":"Worcester, Worcester